  "text": "The Envoy HTTP filter chain configuration propagates from the data-plane-api proto definitions to the C++ implementation through a multi-layered architecture:\n\n## Proto Definition (data-plane-api)\n\nThe configuration is defined in `envoyproxy/data-plane-api` at `envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto`:\n\n1. **HttpConnectionManager** (message, line 43): The main configuration message that defines HTTP connection manager behavior. Contains field `repeated HttpFilter http_filters = 5;` (line 471) which holds the ordered list of HTTP filters to be applied to requests.\n\n2. **HttpFilter** (message, line 1339): Defines individual filter configuration in the chain with:\n   - `string name` (line 1348): Filter name identifier\n   - `google.protobuf.Any typed_config` (line 1358): Static filter configuration\n   - `config.core.v3.ExtensionConfigSource config_discovery` (line 1368): Dynamic configuration source\n   - `bool disabled` (line 1382): Whether filter is disabled by default\n\n## C++ Configuration Parsing (envoy)\n\nThe configuration consumption follows this flow:\n\n### 1. Factory Registration (config.h/config.cc)\n\n**HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory** (`source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h`, line 53) is the main entry point:\n- Extends `ExceptionFreeFactoryBase<envoy::extensions::filters::network::http_connection_manager::v3::HttpConnectionManager>`\n- Implements `createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped()` (config.cc, line 275) which receives the proto config\n- Delegates to `createFilterFactoryFromProtoAndHopByHop()` (config.cc, line 283) which:\n  - Creates singletons for date provider, route config manager, etc. via `Utility::createSingletons()`\n  - Calls `Utility::createConfig()` (config.cc, line 257) to instantiate `HttpConnectionManagerConfig`\n\n### 2. Configuration Object Creation (config.h/config.cc)\n\n**HttpConnectionManagerConfig** (`source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h`, line 127):\n- Implements `Http::FilterChainFactory` interface\n- Constructor (config.cc, ~line 131) processes the proto config:\n  - Creates a `FilterChainHelper<Server::Configuration::FactoryContext, Server::Configuration::NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory>` instance (config.cc, line 709-712)\n  - Calls `helper.processFilters(config.http_filters(), \"http\", \"http\", filter_factories_)` (config.cc, line 714) to parse the http_filters field\n  - Also processes upgrade configs similarly\n\n### 3. Filter Chain Processing (filter_chain_helper.h/cc)\n\n**FilterChainHelper** template class (`source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h`, line 69):\n\n- **processFilters()** method (line 87): Iterates through each `HttpFilter` in the proto's http_filters field, creating a `DependencyManager` and calling `processFilter()` for each\n\n- **processFilter()** method (line 106): For each `HttpFilter` proto message:\n  1. Checks if filter is disabled by default (line 113)\n  2. Validates terminal filter constraints (line 119-123)\n  3. If filter uses config_discovery (line 125-130):\n     - Calls `processDynamicFilterConfig()` to create a dynamic config provider\n  4. Otherwise for typed_config (line 134-164):\n     - Gets the factory via `Config::Utility::getAndCheckFactory()` (line 134)\n     - Translates proto config using `Config::Utility::translateToFactoryConfig()` (line 142)\n     - Creates filter factory callback via `factory->createFilterFactoryFromProto()` (line 145)\n     - Registers filter dependencies (line 150)\n     - Creates static filter config provider (line 155)\n     - Adds to filter_factories list (line 163)\n\n### 4. Filter Chain Instantiation (filter_chain_helper.cc)\n\n**HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain()** (`source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h`, line 141) is called at runtime to instantiate the actual filter chain:\n- Calls `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc, line 17)\n- Iterates through stored filter_factories, checks if disabled, retrieves config provider\n- Applies each filter factory callback to the `FilterChainManager` to instantiate filters in order\n\n## Key Type/Class Summary\n\n**Proto Level (data-plane-api):**\n- `envoy.extensions.filters.network.http_connection_manager.v3.HttpConnectionManager` - Root config\n- `envoy.extensions.filters.network.http_connection_manager.v3.HttpFilter` - Filter definition\n\n**C++ Level (envoy):**\n- `Envoy::Extensions::NetworkFilters::HttpConnectionManager::HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory` - Factory\n- `Envoy::Extensions::NetworkFilters::HttpConnectionManager::HttpConnectionManagerConfig` - Config holder\n- `Envoy::Http::FilterChainHelper<...>` - Filter chain parser\n- `Envoy::Http::FilterChainUtility` - Filter chain instantiation"
